# plot random numbers
fig, *ax = plt.subplots(1,10,figsize=(16,20))
predict = model.predict_classes(x_test)

for i_ax in ax[0]:
    ind = np.random.randint(0,shape[0])
    img = x_test[ind]
    i_ax.imshow(img[:,:,0],cmap='gray')
    if predict[ind] == 10:
        smt = 'It is blank!'
    else:
        smt = 'It is a {}'.format(predict[ind])
    i_ax.set_title(smt)

Problems¶

  • Deal with misalignment of numbers
  • Deal with spaces
  • Character data sets like MNIST don't have dashes
  • Different sizes of images
  • Better deal with noise
  • Make OCR more robust

Connectionist Temporal Classiﬁcation¶

  • Loss function to deal where you don't know where the characters will be in image
  • Works well with RNN's
  • CTC object for a single X,Y pair is:

$P(Y|X) = \sum_{All-Valid} \prod_{t=1}^{T} p_t(a_t|X)$

  • Need a way to deal with duplicate characters
  • We introduce a null symbol $\epsilon$ to split characters or end words

Beam Search¶

  • Want to find the most likely alignment path

$Y^* = argmax P(Y|X)$

  • Simple approach is to take the maximum probability path
  • There could be different paths that collapse into the same string and add up to be more than the max probability path

  • Be general purpose to read all useful data from ID

Building Network in Keras¶

  • Keras allows for rapid prototyping of network architecture
  • Keras isn't made for using loss functions like CTC so some hacks are needed
  • Has flexibility of tensorflow so users can use state of art methods

Deciding Network Architecture¶

  • Read papers, look at other examples, talk to people
  • Transfer learn if possible
  • Prototyping networks require scaled down parameters so fitting is fast
  • Network should be able to memorize subset of data
  • Set up quick benchmarks to test different activations, number of neurons, and optimizers
  • Be prepared that no of it will work (deep learning is still an art)

Other Tips and Tricks¶

  • Make models separate to notebooks
  • Figure out what a good cost actually means
  • If your model is unstable, try batch normalization
